body.description: Introducing the babyGap Deluxe Explorer Wagon by Delta Children: The most responsibly made wagon. Designed for the future in every possible way, all the soft fabric is made from recycled water bottles. Plastic drinking bottles are sorted, cleaned and shredded into flakes that become the yarn the seat fabric is made from. A great choice for your child and the planet, this versatile wagon features two cushioned seats with three-point safety harnesses for security while the removable center console with two cup holders and storage pocket allows kids to share snacks, toys and drinks. Two additional cup holders for parents and side pockets ensure you can bring everything you need along for the adventure. The removable, UV blocking canopy and roll-down shades offer privacy and protection from the sun or rain. Easy to drive, it features swivel front wheels that allow you to effortlessly turn and pivot, as well as push and pull leatherette handles with adjustable heights. The wagon’s compact fold makes it easy to store or transport. And when your children outgrow the need for a wagon, use it to haul your own gear at the farmers market, while gardening or the grocery store. Holds up to 110 lbs. (55 lbs. per seat). Weighs 38 lbs. Recommended for ages 9 months up to 55 lbs.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 27, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This was exactly what I needed. Fits both kids comfortably, 2.5 year old and 9 month old. Super sturdy and and very spacious. Yes the reviews are accurate about the handle bar not being stiff like orders but it is because they bend in order to be sealed. It came already assembled except the top which comes prepared just has to be hooked to the actual stroller wagon, light weight and compactable. If you are looking for am affordable wagon that us useful and looks great, do it!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 4, 2023
reviews.reviewText: best purchase I ever made. So much space and storage for everything my 7 month old needs. Will be able to use for years. Seat belt for safety and large enough to nap in when needed. Shade covers and netting are great. Foldable to fit in car and made very well. Only thing I don’t like is how heavy it is but everything else is so awesome it doesn’t even matter ! If your looking for a good wagon at a decent price this is the one ! And the black camo looks sick and my boy looks so cool riding in it

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Color Me Thrilled
reviews.reviewText: This wagon is an absolute gem! I am, so, SO happy with my purchase. It’s sturdy, versatile as heck, gorgeous (as far as wagons can be, haha), suuuuper easy to put together, locks easily, is comfortable for the kids (I’ve had all three in it already) and has so many options (hello, storage space, cup holders, comfy bottom, great harnesses).
